{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "DVLA to not share details with parking firms unless the individual consents.",
        "additional_details": "Currently DVLA have lawful reasons to share our personal details with civil parking organisations (for a fee). I believe DVLA sharing personal information in this way infringes my privacy, and the privacy of the millions of vehicle users in the country. We trust DVLA to safeguard our information but we believe they fail to do so.",
        "background": "DVLA currently shares our personal details with private parking organisations under Regulation 27 of the Road Vehicles (Registration and Licensing) Regulation 2002. I want this regulation rescinded, and DVLA to only be able to share personal information when they have an individual's permission.",
